result.execSummary:
The defendant Donald C Ancke was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Methamphetamine, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Donald C Ancke in court with attorney Martin Jarvis.  Defendant Donald C Ancke in custody.  Daniel Patrick Steffen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Plea Agreement & Waiver of Rights submitted to the court.  Jarvis makes statement - currently incarcerated in MN.  Interstate agreement in place.  Agreement to plea to amended charge ct 1 to strike enhancer, 1 yr jail with work release, concurrent with prision sentence in Minnesota and serve in Minnesota.  3 days credit.  Court addresses def re: plea/waiver of rights.  Court is satifisfied that def is knowily and freely waiving his rights, finds factual basis. Motion to amend Ct 1 removing enhancer.  Def enters guilty plea.  Court accepts plea.  Joint recommendation is appropriate, DA Winton requests court adopt those as set forth for the disposition.  Statutory court costs.  Jarvis makes statement.  1 yr jail time, concurrent to prison term, eligible for work release.  Allowed to serve sentence in Minnesota.  If eligible to be released from MN and time has not been served in full for WC time, he will return to Washburn.  60dtp fine. Credit for 3 days served.  JOC to be noted with intent to spend incarceration in MN prison. Notice of PCR filed.
